\begin_layout Chapter
Analysis Strategy
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The core of the analysis is the measurement of the top quark spin asymmetries.
 Those can be caculated from the differential 
\begin_inset Formula ${\textstyle \frac{d\sigma}{d\cos\theta}}$
\end_inset

 distributions, where the angle 
\begin_inset Formula $\cos\theta$
\end_inset

 is calculated between the spin bases (spectator jet or beamline) and the
 spin-analyzers (muon, b-tagged jet or neutrino) in the top quark rest frame.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The analysis strategy can be divided into the following two steps will are
 described in detail in this chapter:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Measurement of single the top t-channel differential 
\begin_inset Formula ${\textstyle \frac{d\sigma}{d\cos\theta}}$
\end_inset

 distributions from data using multivariant analysis techniques.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Unfolding of the distributions to correct for reconstruction and detector
 effects.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A cross check is performed by testing the analysis strategy with the generated
 anomalous coupling samples.
\end_layout

