\begin_layout Section
Unfolding
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
After event selection and an additional cut on a MVA discriminator a single
 top t-channel signal containing less background can be obtain from data.
 A caculation of the top spin asymmetries from that can not yet be compared
 to the theory prediction.
 This is due to the smearing effects, finite resolution and the acceptance
 of the detector and from the conducted cuts which bias the differential
 
\begin_inset Formula ${\textstyle \frac{d\sigma}{d\cos\theta}}$
\end_inset

-shape.
 Unfolding is a method to correct these effects from a measured distribution.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Introduction
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
checkthis{check hole section if x->true, y->measured!}
